  "text": "Myrmicinae species were observed in all sites, mainly in those where the soil presents high amounts of lateritic concretions, which provide stable galleries under a thick layer of leaf litter. According to [CITATION_1] , this soil feature supports dense populations of Myrmicinae that allow vertical migrations when conditions become unsuitable for ground nesting, particularly during the rainy season when such soils become too wet.",
